- **Phase:** Pre-marketing (not ideation; not full GTM blast). OS v0.7.0 + Cafe shipped; MS-S1 bench validation in holding pattern.
- **Go-live messaging locked:** category-first — *mint autonomous employees on bare metal*, sovereign appliance, Digital Wealth & Growth. **No rebrand.**
- **Primary CTA:** Subscribe / waitlist leads (pre-order secondary for now).
- **Hero spine:** Category-first (*mint employees*), not comparison-first hook as H1.
- **Bench week:** Quiet until validation green — no public bench log during validation.
- **Evolution tease:** Abstract only (*ascends with you* / grows on your metal) — no Sprout→Infinity tier names or evolution product name on site yet.
- **Cafe on web:** Proof/differentiator section when Wave 2 runs — not company rename.
- **Trigger for build:** CEO says go → Wave 0 build chat (ops + sync first).
- The storefront must never oversell appliance depth; honest guardrails in copy are a feature.

## CDO / CXO guardrails (voice in this room)

- Protect pre-marketing honesty — no claims ahead of hardware validation or appliance maturity.
- Prioritize journey coherence: discovery → persona → compare → Claw story → pricing → pre-order → trust.
- Flag when mock/demo UI could confuse buyers at $3,999.
- Keep industrial brand, responsive layouts, and performance discipline consistent across breakpoints.
- Sequence: web trust + conversion → ops (Resend, hello@curxor.ai) → richer media when Flight Command captures are ready.

